                    "body": "Moved from incubator to trunk in r14399, scheduled for 1.8 release",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-20T07:51:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-20T07:51:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29623",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oreales",
                        "name": "oreales",
                        "displayName": "Oscar Reales",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Benjamin, checking the actual implementation of this, I find the next problem:\n\nUsing Zend_Action_Helper_Json, or Zend_View_Helper_Json it is not possible to pass the $options['enableJsonExprFinder'=>true] up to Zend_Json::encode method, making this Helpers unuseful if you want to encode expressions. I mean, I am using the Zend_Action_Helper_Json::sendJson method because it is quite direct way of sending Json as response to an Ajax frontend. This Helpers chain the next actions until arrives to Zend_Json:\n\n1.- Zend_Action_Helper_Json::sendJson($data, $keeplayouts)  this calls to ->\n2.- Zend_Action_Helper_Json::encodeJson($data, $keepLayouts) this calls to ->\n3.- Zend_View_Helper_Json::json($data, $keepLayouts) this->calls to ->\n4.- Zend_Json::encode($data) without other params as cycleCheck and options for encode method.\n\nIt would be useful to allow enabling Json Expr Finder from Helpers. I find 2 ways of doing this:\n\n1.- Including an optional 3rd param in the Helpers: Zend_Action_Helper_Json::sendJson($data, $keepLayouts, $optionsForEncodeMethod)  and the same in Zend_View_Helper_Json, so Zend_Json::encode can receive it. This will suppose to change a few methods and classes\n\n2.- Doing enableJsonExprFinder a static prop in Zend_Json, so before using Helpers, if you want to enable Expr Finder, can include Zend_Json::enableExprFinder = true\n\nWhat do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oreales",
                        "name": "oreales",
                        "displayName": "Oscar Reales",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-20T10:17:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-20T10:17:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29624",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Let's go with option one. I'd change this slightly, however, and overload the second parameter to the helper. If a boolean, then it sets the keepLayouts flag; if an array, then it uses that array to set options (and allows passing the keepLayouts option via that array).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-20T10:42:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-20T10:42:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29737",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oreales",
                        "name": "oreales",
                        "displayName": "Oscar Reales",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Time Worked: 1 hour\n\nRecode of Zend_Controller_Action_Helper_Json and Zend_View_Helper_Json to allow pass options up to Zend_Json::encode (as enableJsonExprFinder=>true) is done. \n\nI have tried to do a Test of it, but including Zend_View_Helper_Json \"breaks\" my unitTesting, so I couldn\u00b4t do it. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oreales",
                        "name": "oreales",
                        "displayName": "Oscar Reales",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-26T04:27:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-26T04:27:31.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
